                      STAR TREK: THE MOTION PICTURES
                          QUICK REFERENCE GUIDE
                             ORIGINAL SERIES


Ep#   Air Date   Prod#   Title

  1.  12/07/79           The Motion Picture

        When a destructive space entity is spotted approaching Earth,
        Admiral Kirk resumes command of the Starship Enterprise in order
        to intercept, examine, and hopefully stop it.

  2.   6/04/82           The Wrath of Khan

        Admiral Kirk's midlife crisis is interrupted by the return of an
        old enemy looking for revenge and a potentially destructive
        device.

  3.   6/01/84           The Search for Spock

        Admiral Kirk and his bridge crew risk their careers stealing the
        decommissioned Enterprise to return to the restricted Genesis
        planet to recover Spock's body.

  4.  11/26/86           The Voyage Home

        To save Earth from an alien probe, Kirk and his crew go back in
        time to retrieve the only beings who can communicate with it --
        humpback whales.

  5.   6/09/89           The Final Frontier

        Capt. Kirk and his crew must deal with Mr. Spock's half brother
        who hijacks the Enterprise in an obsessive search for God.

  6.  12/06/91           The Undiscovered Country

        The crews of the Enterprise and the Excelsior must stop a plot to
        derail a peace treaty between the Klingon Empire and the
        Federation.


                      STAR TREK: THE MOTION PICTURES
                          QUICK REFERENCE GUIDE
                             NEXT GENERATION


Ep#   Air Date   Prod#   Title

  7.  11/18/94           Generations

        Capt. Picard, with the help of supposedly dead Capt. Kirk, must
        stop a madman willing to murder on a planetary scale in order to
        enter a space nexus.

  8.  11/22/96           First Contact

        Capt. Picard and his crew pursue the Borg back in time to stop
        them from interfering with Earth's first contact with alien life.

  9.  12/11/98           Insurrection

        When the crew of the Enterprise learn of a Federation plot against
        the inhabitants of a unique planet, Capt. Picard begins an open
        rebellion.

 10.  12/09/02           Nemesis

        After the Enterprise is diverted to Romulus, supposedly because
        the Romulans want to negotiate a truce, they soon discover a grave
        threat to the Earth.

